Model training adhered to generally accepted deep-learning practices, adjusted for dataset-specific requirements. The training parameters included an adaptive learning rate via the optimizer, regularization techniques to mitigate overfitting, and diversified epochs ensuring both convergence and generalization. Training and validation processes utilized identical configurations to ensure the integrity of comparisons across datasets such as CIFAR-10 \cite{Krizhevsky2009learning}, CelebA-HQ \cite{Karras2017progressive}, and LSUN church and bedroom categories \cite{Yu2015lsun} after preprocessing for consistency.

